This paper discusses a technique for reducing the number of fitness evaluations in the Bayesian optimization algorithm, which is commonly used in machine learning and optimization problems. The paper focuses on extending Bayesian networks to estimate fitness for newly sampled candidate solutions, which is a key aspect of the BOA. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are both concerned with developing algorithms that can learn from data. The paper also involves optimization, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves modeling and sampling, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible sub-category as well.
